Bash Paramters(Variables)
    Variables are parameters set with a name on the left of an equal sign and a value on the right side.
    Variables are user defined.
Special Parameters(Builtin Variables)
    $ SPECIAL PARAMETERS
        $#  -  represents # of args passd to shell script
        $0  -  represents the script name
        $i  -  gives the ith argument passed to the shell script
        $*  -  gives all args passed to the shell script seperated by a space
        $!  -  gives the PID of the last background running process
        $?  -  
        $_  -  gives last argument provided to the last command that executed
        $$  -  gives the PID of the current shell
        $@  -  
        $-  -  represents current flags set in your shell
Functions
